<paragraph blockId="88.[189,1399,265,397]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">ABDOMEN. Oval, comparatively narrow, width of tergite II posteriorly equal to mesonotum width at level of wing base, shiny laterally and grey-brown pollinose medially on all tergites, covered with comparatively short white, erect pilosity laterally and short white and black adpressed pilosity medially. Other characters as in male.</paragraph>
